# Shopify Polaris Design System Guide for Vue Components

## How to Use This Guide

This file is a **Cursor project rule** that automatically gets included in every AI conversation within this workspace. When you ask the AI to create or style Vue components, it will use these Polaris design tokens and patterns.

### Usage Examples:

**Creating new components:**
> "Create a WeWeb button component in Polaris style with primary, secondary, and destructive variants"

**Styling existing components:**
> "Style this form component to match Shopify Polaris"

**Specific patterns:**
> "Add a Polaris-style card with header, body, and footer sections"

### Key Points:
- All CSS custom properties use the `--p-` prefix (Polaris convention)
- Components follow the `.polaris-*` class naming convention
- Design tokens are comprehensive - use them instead of hardcoded values
- Follow the component patterns section for consistent structure

